tiles.markdown:
## RP Monitoring
***

## 1. Splunk

* [RP userinfo](https://gds.splunkcloud.com/en-GB/app/search/search?q=search%20index%3D%22gds_di_prod_txma-performance%22%20USER_INFO_RETURNED%20%7C%20timechart%20count%20by%20client_id&display.page.search.mode=smart&dispatch.sample_ratio=1&workload_pool=&earliest=-30m%40m&latest=now&sid=1732277796.50064&display.page.search.tab=visualizations&display.general.type=visualizations&display.visualizations.charting.chart=line)
* [RP Tokens](https://gds.splunkcloud.com/en-GB/app/search/search?q=search%20index%3D%22gds_di_production%22%20source%3D%22533266965190%3A%2Faws%2Flambda%2Fproduction-token-lambda*%22%20message%3D%22Successfully%20generated%20tokens%22%20%7C%20timechart%20count%20by%20client-id&display.page.search.mode=smart&dispatch.sample_ratio=1&workload_pool=&earliest=-30m%40m&latest=now&display.page.search.tab=visualizations&display.general.type=visualizations&display.visualizations.charting.chart=line&sid=1732278051.50163)

## 2. Confluence

* [TSD - 24/7 Monitoring - RP Splunk Queries](https://govukverify.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/OPS/pages/4758175970/TSD+-+24+7+Monitoring+-+RP+Splunk+Queries)

## 3. Dynatrace Data Explorer query.
To get client ID Vs Name.
Go into data explorer and use below query in advance mode.
* 
[Client ID Vs Name](https://bhe21058.live.dynatrace.com/ui/data-explorer?gtf=-2h&gf=all#)

cloud.aws.authentication.signInExistingAccountByClientByAccountIdClientClientNameEnvironmentLogGroupRegionServiceNameServiceType:filter(and(or(eq(environment,production)))):splitBy(clientname,client):count:sort(value(avg,descending))

Points to remember
* SuccessfulTokenIssued is indicator that Onelogin has authenticated/proved identity the user and passed back to RP. This basically is a token that onelogin sends to RP with a time to live which is consumed by the RP systems. This is common for Auth and Identity journey. If there is big dip in token metrics and at the same time, there is traffic on signin, then it could be an indicator of issue with one login.
* UserInfoReturned is not be used by all RPs. Some dont fetch user information after receiving token.
